hs|nd|nt|Before we go on to the next deal, there are a few interesting points to be made about the bidding of this deal. We would always open the bidding with Sheri's 11 HCP hand regardless of the position or vulnerability. The 3 quick tricks, good spot cards and possible lead-direct in diamonds, the singleton, and no rebid problems, all help make 1@D pretty clear as far as we are concerned.|
pg| ***** 22 ***** |


hs|ns|ls|nd|
nt|We also like Sheri's 2@S rebid (versus 2@C). Fred and Sheri usually have 4-card support to raise in this situation (which is one of the reasons that Fred bid 4@S), but Sheri thought it was best to limit her (very minimum) opening as quickly as possible. That fact that Sheri's spades were considerably stronger than her clubs also contributed to this good decision.|
pg| ***** 23 ***** |


ls|ns|hs|ss|nt|Fred's 4@S rebid was not a particularly good bid (we like 3NT in retrospect), but, as we mentioned, Sheri would always deliver either a 4th trump or a ruffing value for her raise to 2@S. We don't know where Fred and Sheri would have ended up if Fred had rebid 3NT, but we doubt you would be reading about it in ^*BThe Deal of the Week^*N!|
