nt|The actual card combination that Fred faced was not exactly the same, but it was not too difficult for him to figure out that it was still right to start by leading the @SQ with this combination as well. Many experts think it is correct to cash the @SA first and lead low to dummy's @SQ on the second round (picking up @SJx with RHO). That plan is inferior.|
