nt|Leading the @SQ from dummy on the first round of the suit also picks up @SJx with RHO, but this play gains in that it picks up @SKx with RHO as well. All other 4-2 and 3-3 breaks cancel out. The @SQ play loses to a singleton @SK or @SJ with either defender, but these 4 5-1 splits are not as likely as the 4 4-2 splits that @SKx with RHO represent.|
